name: National University
directions: Through main entrance and to the right. Gender-neutral is on the right, near the staff/faculty lounge.
comment: The campus is open to all- ok to use if you're not a student.

name: Target
directions: Next to gendered restrooms

name: Laemmle
directions: Family bathroom down the same hall as the men's and woman's bathrooms

name: Starbucks
comment: Bathroom is locked, ask person at the walk-up window to buzz you in. They will do so even if you are not a customer, so long as it is not right before close.

name: Guardian Games
directions: Far nw corner, in hallway.
comment: Browser a bit, friendly staff

name: Guardian Games
directions: Far back of the store, nw corner
comment: Browse a bit. Friendly staff!

name: Cineplex VIP
directions: In VIP Area but ask

name: Wendy's/Marathon
directions: Through the Marathon section, by the drinks.
comment: Transgender staff, familiar with trans folks using the facilities here.

name: Mills Gallery at Boston Center for the Arts
directions: In the back, follow exit signs (next to back emergency exit) or ask gallery attendant

name: The Bistro
comment: Bar hours only, must be 21

name: Vintage Stock
directions: In the back of the store
comment: Ask the employees to use the restroom.

name: Target
directions: By the pharmacy, and HBA.
comment: Target supports both trans individuals using restrooms they're comfortable using and also has a single family restroom by the pharmacy.

name: Starbucks
comment: Two gender neutral restrooms

name: Half Price Books
directions: On opposite end of building from front doors, between the Computers/Internet and Foreign Language & Clearance sections.
comment: Two single toilet rooms both marked with unisex signs.

name: Double Dippers
directions: In the back of the shop past the ice cream. Bathroom has a handicap rail, though the hallway leading to the bathroom looked a little narrow.
comment: Must be a paying customer to use. The parlor is gay owned and the worker I talked to was very nice! They have some pamphlets including a LGBT+ resource guide for Rehoboth Beach that you can pick up for free.

name: Sam's Club
directions: To the left of the gendered restrooms, towards the pharmacy
comment: Family bathroom

name: Harry's Ocean Bar and Grill
directions: One unisex/family bathroom in same hallway as gendered bathrooms

name: Spice
directions: It is all the way in the back on the ground floor
comment: This is a restaurant, so you may have to actually be eating there to use it. Or try asking the person at the front desk.

name: Public Bathroom
street: 6155 S Main St Unit E-112 Aurora, CO  80016 United States
directions: Walk past Sunglasses hut, away from the Main Street and take a left into the bathrooms.
comment: There are 2 small rooms, presumably for breastfeeding or diaper changing. One of the rooms have a curtain the other doesn't.

name: Eaglecrest High School
street: 5100 S Picadilly St Aurora CO 80015-3300 United States
directions: Walk into the cafeteria then take a left and on your left there is 2 gender neutral bathrooms
comment: Only available if enrolled in the school or in the school

name: Lift Breakfast Bakery
directions: At the back near the stools in front of the window

name: Red Ginger
comment: Not trans friendly. They refused a gender neutral bathroom sign after the passing of hb2. dont go here.

name: Moonflower community cooperative
comment: Friendly staff and recent gender neutral bathrooms

name: Mayhem Collectibles
directions: At the back of the game room.
comment: Two accessible, gender neutral single stall restrooms

name: Cvph medical center
directions: In the main lobby down the hallway immediately to the left. 3/4 of the way down the hall

name: Hart Theater
street: 1 Empire State Plaza, S Mall Arterial
comment: Handicap-accessible single-stall restroom.

name: Starbucks
directions: Next to Men's Warehouse, in front of the Mall
comment: Literally just walk in and go to the right. You're good fam.

name: Florida Tech Denis Student Center
directions: Second floor
comment: Open to all, students and non-students

name: Bennu Coffee
street: 2001 E Martin Luther King Jr Blvd
directions: Through the front door, past the counter on your right, turn right, and the bathrooms are down the hall.
comment: There are a woman's head silhouette and a man's head silhouette painted on the doors from before, but both bathrooms have new gender-neutral signs next to the doors. Each bathroom has two stalls in it and a sink.

name: Tekapo
directions: At the car park on the south side of town, near the (future) 4 Square supermarket.
comment: Great automated toilets, free, clean, and they talk! 🙂

name: Trader Joes
directions: It is in the back of the store by the beer isle.

name: Vegenation
directions: Straight back through front entrance

name: Target at Eastridge Mall
directions: Turn left when entering from outside entrance doors, located in alcove across from checkout area.
comment: Single occupancy gender neutral restroom

name: Jury Pool
directions: By the locker rooms, there are 2 family restrooms/changing room

name: Lenox Coffee
directions: Through the coffee shop, door on the left (not straight ahead)

name: Books-A-Million
directions: In the back corner, next to the magazines- two restrooms, both gender-neutral.
comment: You don't have to buy anything, but probably browse a bit after you go since it's a store.

name: Wilmette Junior High School
directions: Follow the main hallway on the first floor until just past the teacher's lounge.
comment: This school is a closed campus, and in order to use it you must check in at the main office. They may not let you in during school hours.

name: Honeysuckle Tea House
directions: Around the back of the tea house.

name: El Pollo Loco
comment: Two neutral single stall bathrooms!

name: Vöner
directions: Right from the counter, unmarked white door on the left of the hallway.
comment: For customers, but easy to use anyway since often very crowded.

name: OEB Breakfast
comment: Must be a paying customer.

name: Myxa Café
directions: Keep left to enter the back of the café, then take a right.
comment: For customers, but coffee starts at 1,20€ and is good. Offers free hygiene products (in a box) and has an armchair to wait in front of the restroom.

name: Hamilton 16 IMAX
directions: Family restrooms located in the north and south wings (the two hallways where theaters are located, to either side of concessions)
comment: During most hours, you will need to show an employee a ticket to reach these restrooms.

name: Bodhi Bowl
directions: Hallway to the left, door on the right

name: Starbucks
comment: ask for the code

name: Hilltop Cafe Bistro
directions: In the door to the right

name: Veteran's Memorial Leisure Center
directions: Enter through main enterance to front desk, take a right

name: First Friends Meeting
comment: All restrooms inside the church are all gender

name: FedEx Office Print and Ship center
directions: Straight ahead

name: Paradise Cafe
directions: Northwest corner by the exit sign.

name: Fair Game
directions: Go through the big blue door and down the hallway. Bathroom is on the left.
comment: Owners are very queer-friendly

name: Kiwanis Park
comment: Two gender neutral single bathrooms by the dog park.

name: The Gundis
directions: All gender bathroom in back next to gendered bathrooms

name: Albanese Candy Factory
directions: Straight ahead from the entrance, a bit to the left. Near an employees only door which is easier to see from the entrance.
comment: Single stall family restroom. Plus, awesome candy store.

name: Hart Theater at The Egg
directions: Near even-numbered doors to theater.
comment: Handicap-accessible single-stall.

name: Freys Hotel
directions: Ask at the reception for the directions and the key code.
comment: The hotel is very lgbt friendly, so there should be no problem with using it even if you are not a guest.

name: Weser Blue Bar
directions: It is not directly located at the bar but about 50 meters away behind the playground in a seperate small iron building.
comment: The bar is only there in summer but the toilet is there permanently. Might require a small fee (50 cents) to use it.

name: Starbucks
directions: First floor in corner.
comment: Two single stall unisex restrooms.

name: The Park Cafe
directions: Right by the door.
comment: Probably for patrons but it's worth eating here, it was terrific!

name: Slightly North of Broad
directions: Both restrooms in the restaurant are single stall and gender neutral
comment: This is a high end restaurant so it's probably accessible to patrons only. I actually don't know if it's accessible for mobility issues or not, sorry!

name: Starbucks
directions: On the right from the front door

name: Manhasset School (Next to Black Box)
directions: Right next to the black box theatre room.
comment: You can ask Fess (Mr. Fessler) about it.

name: Nicolaysen Art Museum
directions: Second floor, go up stairs behind front desk and turn right down short corridor.  Bathroom is on right side in corridor.
comment: Single occupancy gender nuetral bathroom located in part of office/staff area.  Ask receptionist at front desk in lobby - I needed the facility while attending a recent event at the museum and the receptionist was friendly and accommodating of my needs.
